1039.name: Tidal Song
1039.hero_desc:
A core member of Division Nine in Aether Gazer. Poseidon is more proficient at using Divine Power to provide support to her teammates than fighting head-on with Visbanes.
She is gentle and quiet, and is good at listening to the troubles of others.
1039.impression: I've been witness to how far you have come, Admin. You've grown and become a core member of Division Nine despite having lost your memories. I think, apart from your innate talents and abilities, you must have felt a lot of pressure from the people around you too. If only I could help take some of that pressure off you, Admin... For example, by being your counsellor or something like that. Actually, since you've already come to me to share your problems and ask for my advice on several occasions, you must trust me very much. In reciprocation, I will also share what's on my mind with you, Admin. I hope that one day, we will be able to speak completely freely with each other...
1039.weapon_desc: Poseidon's Divine Power is one of the few that can repair Modifiers' core data in battle. The Cryptics used the legendary trident as a model to design an Access Key to help Poseidon control this energy better. A beautiful sound like a wave is emitted occasionally when the Divine Power is used, so it got the name Tidal Song.

1048.name: Comet R4Y
1048.hero_desc: Lively, carefree Zenkibo is the biggest troublemaker in Aether Gazer. She spends all her excess energy on pulling pranks and claims to have an invisible friend called Goki. No one knows if Goki exists or not.
1048.impression:
Why do I like to play pranks on Admin so much? Hmm, where do I even begin... Admin's reactions are always hilarious, and they always forgive me quickly. But more importantly, Admin always knows what I want, takes me out to play when I'm bored, and comforts me when I'm down. It's always lovely to be with Admin!
Hmm... What should I do with Admin next time...? It's no longer enough to play a prank on Admin... I know! Maybe it's time for Admin and I to have a prank contest to see who can play the biggest prank on the other person! It'll be so fun, and I know I'll emerge on top as the Master of Pranks!
1048.weapon_desc: The full name is: Comet R4Y Ct-08 Self-generating Beam Rifle. The gun body contains a compression of a high concentration of light particles, and the Energy is transferred through an inbuilt fusion device. It can fire a large, powerful cannon-like electric charge at the pull of a trigger. The latest scientific achievement of The Cryptics.

1066.name: Early Sakura
1066.hero_desc:
A young girl who joined Aether Gazer on the condition that she would be allowed free rein to research and invent. She is currently working as a member of The Cryptics.
Ookuninushi hardly participates in combat against Visbanes, and seems only interested in inventions and tarot cards.
1066.impression: Truthfully, as an assistant Admin is not quite useful, and the most I can ask them to do is to help out with the manual work. However, although Admin has not been blessed by the God of Truth, they can actually understand my inventions through sheer logic alone. This is something even other scientists can't do! In the past, I never expected to be understood by anyone... But maybe Admin has become a very important person to me without me even realizing it.
1066.weapon_desc: Ookuninushi's inventions: BunBun-1: BunBun Iron Fist, BunBun-2: BunBun Laser Gun, BunBun-3: BunBun Mecha!

1038.name: Radiant Feather
1038.hero_desc:
Hera is a Modifier who belongs to the Society of Muses and is also a famous lady from the Omorfies Sephirah Zone.
She is the ladiest of ladies, known far and wide for her beauty, elegance, and aesthetic taste.
1038.weapon_desc: This scepter is set with red stones said to be precious garnets, brought over by the Phoenix. Divine Power can be unleashed when holding the scepter and using it as a medium. It can also summon the Phoenix to explore or launch attacks on enemies.

1099.name: Sakubo
1099.hero_desc:
A Modifier who holds herself to incredible standards, and serves as the leader of the Pheasant Squad.
Tsukuyomi does not say much, but her combat analysis is concise, and she is someone her team trusts with any task.
1099.impression:
To be honest, I knew there was something special about the Admin the first time we met. I could sense their aura, which was gentle yet uniquely powerful. The Admin may be human, but they've never shied away from facing Visbanes head-on, and they're always willing to put their life on the line for their friends... It's impossible for me to not admire the Admin for this.
Before I met the Admin, my life was all about the sword. However, I've since realized that there are many other things around me. Furthermore, the Admin seems to care more about me as a person than my talents and skills... Only when I'm with the Admin can I let my hair down for a while.
1099.weapon_desc:
A pair of swords used by Sasanami warriors in numerous missions to behead their targets. The katana Saku has a swift and dexterous fighting style, but every swing of Saku builds up the Dark Side for the other blade, Bo.
When the Dark Side of the Moon completely covers Bo, an excessive desire for combat emerges in Tsukuyomi, and she must unleash this power with a completely different fighting style.

1084.name: New Pact
1084.hero_desc:
Verthandi is a member of the Rookie Squad who just passed the tests required to join Aether Gazer's Special Task Force, and she's always full of energy.
Her optimistic and outgoing personality is so strong that it seems nothing can bring her down.
1084.weapon_desc: This longsword, which symbolizes destiny and fate, is also known as the Sword of Heroes. Before it was made into an Access Key, it was a holy sword, known throughout the world. Its wielders were all heroes who achieved glorious feats, or the ones chosen by this sword were fated to become heroes from the very beginning. The ridge of the sword is engraved with a line of unreadable ancient Runic text. It seems to be an ancient poetic ballad from an icy region.

1093.name: Jin-ei
1093.hero_desc: You'll likely find this stealthy white-haired Mod at all the big festivals. She is rather cynical, and likes to tease her juniors.
1093.weapon_desc:
A legendary and famous sword of Sasanami, rumored to have been owned by a great general, which can split lightning falling from the sky.
It was transformed by The Cryptics into a set of ninja swords, one long and one short, with a special scabbard and mobile device that improves peak performance for infiltration missions.

1019.name: Gusty Lance
1019.hero_desc: From a practical point of view, Shu is really the one who handles Aether Gazer's administrative duties. She is not only the one responsible for training the future Administrator, she's also admired by her younger comrades and trusted by her seniors to help out with all sorts of tasks.
1019.impression: Quietly and quite out of the blue, the Administrator has become a key pillar of Division Nine. I've expected great things from you, Admin, ever since I became your mentor. But I didn't expect such tremendous progress from you, and frankly, there's nothing more gratifying for a teacher to see. No matter how strong you are, there are times you will get tired. Furthermore, an Administrator of Division Nine carries great responsibilities on their shoulders. You can always come to me if you need someone to lean on, Admin. You're my student, as well as someone who's personally important to me.
1019.weapon_desc: An Access Key that can control the flow of air. It was once used in ancient times as an instrument to pray for good weather. After it became an Access Key, The Cryptics transformed into the shape of a lance for Shu. It sends down a mysterious substance known as "Sacred Gale Crystals" during battle. The composition of these crystals cannot be analyzed, and they dissipate in the wind minutes after causing damage. The hypothesis is that they are metals brought from another dimension by the abnormal airflow.

1080.name: Frost Fang
1080.hero_desc: A Modifier brought back from an ice-sealed section of a Sephirah Zone. Her years of living alone have left her with a cold, unapproachable look, and she's not quite able to socialize.
1080.weapon_desc: Vidar has carried this weapon around with her since her awakening. It looks unimpressive, and everyone treats it as a hunting axe she had sharpened with ice. It was supposedly once thrown into an ice hole in the polar region by a group of humans, and stayed in the ice until Vidar awakened as a Modifier and retrieved it. After joining Aether Gazer, The Cryptics made some modifications to the weapon. It can easily create cold air in the places the axe blade has cut, causing the temperature in the area to fall below zero.

1027.name: Drifting Flurry
1027.hero_desc:
Leviathan is always full of energy, and a real ditzy cutie pie.
She is naive and lively, but is unexpectedly the jealous sort. Do not act like you are close with Vidar in front of her.
1027.impression: Admin is really smart! Without Admin, I'd have failed Labbi's test and never activated my Access Key. And Admin's really capable too: it was Admin's tutoring that helped me pass my tests and get into the survey team. And oh, oh, Admin has helped walk Fenrir, bought me ice cream, and even told Zenkibo to go easy on me with her pranks... Admin has always taken such good care of me, and I want to always be with Admin, too. When I have Admin with me, it feels like I can do anything!
1027.weapon_desc:
Leviathan found this anchor in an ice cave, and it is not the typical size and weight of an ice breaker ship's anchor.
It looks like some mariner's souvenir. Its exterior has been corroded by the ice and snow. The Cryptics modified it into what is now Leviathan's favorite weapon.

1050.name: Shinku
1050.hero_desc: Buzenbo has trained in traditional kendo ever since she was little. Besides learning how to conquer her enemies with her blade, she's also absorbed the kendo spirit of protecting the weak, observing manners and restraint, and respecting her master.
1050.weapon_desc: The blade is said to have been brought by Yatagarasu and once served as an important treasure for Sasanami to guard its national fortunes, but was later lost in a civil war. It is known to the world as the ancestor of katanas.

1148.name: Surefire
1148.hero_desc: Lively, carefree Zenkibo is the biggest troublemaker in Aether Gazer. She spends all her excess energy on pulling pranks and claims to have an invisible friend called Goki. No one knows if Goki exists or not.
1148.impression:
Why do I like to play pranks on Admin so much? Hmm, where do I even begin... Admin's reactions are always hilarious, and they always forgive me quickly. But more importantly, Admin always knows what I want, takes me out to play when I'm bored, and comforts me when I'm down. It's always lovely to be with Admin!
Hmm... What should I do with Admin next time...? It's no longer enough to play a prank on Admin... I know! Maybe it's time for Admin and I to have a prank contest to see who can play the biggest prank on the other person! It'll be so fun, and I know I'll emerge on top as the Master of Pranks!
1148.weapon_desc: A mysterious scope set found by the exploration team while exploring an ancient ruin. After it was connected to the Mimir system, they discovered that it contains a large variety of types of Visbane data. The Cryptics modified it into a compound weapon that can take multiple forms, combining frontal breaching and ultra long-range sniping, and can be adapted for almost all combat situations.

1094.name: Darkstar
1094.hero_desc: A girl who does not like to speak with other people and who is always quietly looking at the night sky by herself. It seems she's had some really dark childhood experiences.
1094.weapon_desc: An AI known internally as Ganglati. This rather plain-looking coffin transforms into a powerful arsenal. While full of gripes and vicious of tongue, it becomes as quiet as a church mouse once it is put on the receiving end of a scolding.

1037.name: Dark Mistletoe
1037.hero_desc: Hodur is a member of the Intelligence Office and has an elder twin sister, Baldr. Unlike Hodur, her sister has a bright personality. Yet Hodur always quietly follows Baldr's glow and doesn't show much of herself.
1037.weapon_desc:
Hodur's Access Key is a rare parasitic type that lives in the form of a micro-organism in the body of the Mod since awakening. It brings great power, but also higher, uncontrollable risks.
The Cryptics helped Hodur gain temporary control over the Access Key parasite, limiting it to her right hand. Using a special device, the Divine Power it emits is converted into energy that is blasted at enemies.

1011.name: The Innocence
1011.hero_desc: The most popular Modifier in the headquarters, and affectionally called "Lil' Osi" by everyone. Whenever she finds out a comrade's having trouble, she will do what she can to help, and always puts others above herself.
1011.impression:
Admin has always been someone I can rely on. Unlike me, Admin never shrinks away in the face of difficulty. Instead, they'd bravely forge ahead. Now that I think about it, Admin has always been giving me all sorts of help, and I've only been able to stay here because Admin has always let me know how much faith everyone has in me. What Admin said to me the other time... Has been guiding me forward, like a lighthouse.
Admin has always been so good to me even though I've caused so much trouble for them. I must work even harder, so that I won't let Admin down and that I can continue to be by their side.
1011.weapon_desc: A huge scythe that is disproportionately large. It can easily reap the soul of the person it touches. It was once mentioned in an ancient book, said that this scythe was used to cleanse the soul of the sinners. Duat Scythe was later abandoned when people thought it brought bad luck, and that it would bring about catastrophe whenever it appeared.

1199.name: Shinri
1199.hero_desc:
A Modifier who holds herself to incredible standards, and serves as the leader of the Pheasant Squad.
Tsukuyomi does not say much, but her combat analysis is concise, and she is someone her team trusts with any task.
1199.impression:
To be honest, I knew there was something special about the Admin the first time we met. I could sense their aura, which was gentle yet uniquely powerful. The Admin may be human, but they've never shied away from facing Visbanes head-on, and they're always willing to put their life on the line for their friends... It's impossible for me to not admire the Admin for this.
Before I met the Admin, my life was all about the sword. However, I've since realized that there are many other things around me. Furthermore, the Admin seems to care more about me as a person than my talents and skills... Only when I'm with the Admin can I let my hair down for a while.
1199.weapon_desc:
A set of three blades with three small characters from an ancient civilization engraved at the base of their hilts. Two have been deciphered, "Shin" and "Ri."
The ancient books say they represent two directions, but the exact interpretation cannot be tracked. Swinging the blade causes a disturbance in the surrounding natural elements, covering it with electric currents, which also gave them the name Lightning Fire.

1184.name: Archaic Oath
1184.hero_desc:
Verthandi is a member of the Rookie Squad who just passed the tests required to join Aether Gazer's Special Task Force, and she's always full of energy.
Her optimistic and outgoing personality is so strong that it seems nothing can bring her down.
1184.weapon_desc:
This ancient Access Key recovered from the Source Layer once had a very similar appearance to the Runic Blade, but both the sword hilt and blade have been corroded by chaotic flows. Only the inscription stone embedded in the sword retains the permissions to communicate with the world system. There appears to be a long mark scored across the inscription stone, which is engraved with ancient runic text that reads "Fate." Once activated, the stone continuously draws energy data from the surrounding area.
The Cryptics decided to transform the stone into a protective shield equipped with a set of armor and an energy drainage device that can bear great pressure. The device has been adjusted to fit Verthandi's sword style preference, and effectively channels the absorbed energy to a specific area. The Rune Shield offers great protection even if the inscription stone has not yet been activated.

1058.name: Ryugiri
1058.hero_desc:
Leader of the Karasugo family's Kyū Squad, and a master of skiving off work.
Kagutsuchi loves nothing more than fishing at the lake. He is often troubled by the fact that he's mistaken for a minor due to his appearance.
1058.weapon_desc:
This large long katana forged by the Karasugo Family is said to be able to cut off the heads of creatures as large as dragons.
Records indicate that a secret method may be used to cause the katana to heat up to incredible temperatures, turning the dark patterns a fiery red, thereby unleashing these dragon-like veins in the katana's body.

1059.name: The Glare
1059.hero_desc:
A member of Aether Gazer's Thunder Squad. Good at sniping enemies with a bow and arrow. Claims to have a 100% hit rate.
He is very confident in his skills, and his appearance, but he is often teased by Zenkibo because of it.
1059.weapon_desc: When the bowstring is drawn, it automatically gathers the user's Divine Power to form an arrow that shines like the sun. Because so much power is needed to draw the bow, it is difficult for Mods other than Apollo to use it.

1096.name: Windwalker
1096.hero_desc: The star courier of Olympia Express. Is often spotted weaving through the streets and alleys of the various Sephirah Zones with her massive backpack containing customer packages, conveying love and hope to every single person she meets.
1096.weapon_desc:
A set of leg armor created for Hermes by a young Iris, now CEO of Olympia. The armor is powered by pure tranzist. Was made an Access Key by the Gaea system at the time of Hermes' awakening, as a result of which its form has changed significantly and now has direct access to various system permissions.
Its wearer can burst into a sprint or dash at a speed that is unimaginable for humans.

1026.name: Airgetlam
1026.hero_desc: A mechanical engineer who likes to challenge himself and try odd designs, he has a long-term cooperation with Aether Gazer, and specializes in actualizing The Cryptics' inventions.
1026.weapon_desc: Nuadha used his Modifier abilities to create this box-shaped weapon with a variety of functions, each of which is suited for a different situation. Its design includes the ability to spit scorching flames at enemies, meeting the needs of mid and close range combat.

1097.name: Drowsie
1097.hero_desc: A Modifier with the ability to enter and invite others to enter dreams. Unable to fully control this ability, however, Hades has taken her into the Society of Muses, where Hades' two puppet maids look after her.
1097.weapon_desc: A plush lamb toy called "Drowsie" that is always by Oneiroi's side—Oneiroi is quite convinced that it is alive! Drowsie allows Oneiroi to access the dreams of others, though when Oneiroi loses control the people around her can get sucked into her dreamscape instead. While Drowsie is unable to speak, it has been known to make its way around town on the sly.

1139.name: Arctic Abyss
1139.hero_desc:
A core member of Division Nine in Aether Gazer. Poseidon is more proficient at using Divine Power to provide support to her teammates than fighting head-on with Visbanes.
She is gentle and quiet, and is good at listening to the troubles of others.
1139.impression: I've been witness to how far you have come, Admin. You've grown and become a core member of Division Nine despite having lost your memories. I think, apart from your innate talents and abilities, you must have felt a lot of pressure from the people around you too. If only I could help take some of that pressure off you, Admin... For example, by being your counsellor or something like that. Actually, since you've already come to me to share your problems and ask for my advice on several occasions, you must trust me very much. In reciprocation, I will also share what's on my mind with you, Admin. I hope that one day, we will be able to speak completely freely with each other...
1139.weapon_desc: An Access Key fragment taken out by a white whale from a deep ocean trench, which has been solidified into a biting cold ice crystal by the high pressure of the sea water. The Cryptics modified it into a double-handed staff for Poseidon. In her hands, it exudes great Divine Power, but also makes the user feel an unbearable chill.

1036.name: Baldr
1036.hero_desc: Hodur is a member of the Intelligence Office and has an elder twin sister, Baldr. Unlike Hodur, her sister has a bright personality. Yet Hodur always quietly follows Baldr's glow and doesn't show much of herself.
1036.weapon_desc:
Hodur's Access Key is a rare parasitic type that lives in the form of a micro-organism in the body of the Mod since awakening. It brings great power, but also higher, uncontrollable risks.
The Cryptics helped Hodur gain temporary control over the Access Key parasite, limiting it to her right hand. Using a special device, the Divine Power it emits is converted into energy that is blasted at enemies.

1138.name: Phantasmal Dawn
1138.hero_desc:
Hera is a Modifier who belongs to the Society of Muses and is also a famous lady from the Omorfies Sephirah Zone.
She is the ladiest of ladies, known far and wide for her beauty, elegance, and aesthetic taste.
1138.weapon_desc:
An Access Key that came into existence with the birth of Hera. Shaped by starlight and the light of morn, it has the power to control light.
The more faith gathered in Hera, the stronger the light attached to it.

1013.name: Rāhu
1013.hero_desc: A martial arts enthusiast who travels around, taking on challengers with the aim of becoming the best fighter in the world. She is concerned with nothing other than growing stronger and stronger. She is powerful as hell, but she isn't exactly a sophisticated thinker.
1013.weapon_desc: Vambraces that hold the power of a mighty demon. The classics record the original owner as someone who had maintained an all-time undefeated record, but it seems it has not yet reached complete form...

1056.name: Thundertusk
1056.hero_desc: Kali, a member of Meruism, was taken in by the organization and slowly started to care for the other children that were also taken in. Her character has been tempered to maturity, and she takes pride in her role as an elder sister.
1056.weapon_desc: A simply constructed set of brass knuckles that are capable of withstanding strong electric currents and which can be charged for a power boost. This design allows Kali's power to be unleashed in the most direct manner.

1111.name: Living Soul
1111.hero_desc: While the appearance here is exactly the same as Osiris, the dominant personality is that of the mad, mad Ausar. Has great power, but isn't very keen on working together with the other Modifiers.
1111.impression:
A puny, weak human being who knows nothing but sweet talk, and who has zero value—that was how I used to think of them. But now, I must say I have to eat my words, for they were willing to save someone even at the risk of having fried to a crisp by yours truly. At least they're not somebody who is full of nothing but hot air.
Besides... I suppose Admin is somewhat interesting, so I might as well have some fun with them first. At the very least, I don't have to worry about them stabbing Osiris or myself in the back. So I guess Admin is just about qualified for me to consider them as a friend.
1111.weapon_desc: An Access Key that an Aether Gazer scan discovered in the Source Layer. It was later identified as having Osiris' Aether Code. Contains a great deal of Bane Energy as it had been buried in a heavily corrupted zone for a long time, and can thus severely corrode its user.

1032.name: AblaZe
1032.hero_desc: Heir to the Valleyrand Family. After undertaking a joint venture with Aether Gazer, Tyr joined their Board of Directors and is now the supervisor for Division Three. He rules with an iron fist, and treats business like war, striking fiercely and without remorse.
1032.weapon_desc: Legends say the magic sword brings glory to its wielder, and also an ancient curse. Tyr can summon multiple shadows of this mighty sword, and control them as he wishes, making his battle-style much like playing a round of chess.

1035.name: Croc Rage
1035.hero_desc: A child who grew up in a mountain forest. Even though he awakened as a Modifier, he doesn't care too much about saving the world. Now a member of the Children of Iron, he often wears a crocodile headgear to frighten his enemies.
1035.weapon_desc: Sobek picked up this pair of ancient swords from who-knows-where. Even though their bodies are rusted beyond belief, he still treats them like treasure, and named them Croc Blades. After the Children of Iron polished them for Sobek, these blades regained their long lost luster.

1041.name: Chord of Convallaria
1041.hero_desc: The current commander of the Knights of Convallaria, she is a person of moral integrity who upholds the chivalric values of justice and loyalty. She has made it her lifelong mission to safeguard artistic order in Omorfies.
1041.impression: Admin is a really interesting person. Many people say that I'm really unapproachable with this face and demeanor of mine, but it seems that Admin doesn't care about all that. They treat me like they'd anyone else, and whenever I talk to Admin, I find myself feeling at ease. Admin has also helped broaden my horizons. Thanks to them, I've learned many, many things. I used to think that to maintain order and to uphold justice I'd have to be on my own on what is a long and hard road. But that hasn't been the case at all, because as long as Admin is with me I'm never lonely. Admin is the most important friend in my life.
1041.weapon_desc: An Access Key set consisting of a light and heavy sword that enables the user to employ two different fighting styles simultaneously. It's said that the two swords' special composition makes them play melodious music when they cross over each other.

1042.name: Puppet Master
1042.hero_desc: The person who manages and runs the various Mod activities at the Society of Muses, and thus the one who is actually in charge. Also known as the "youthful witch" for her appearance, which has not changed for the last 30 years, as well as for the menacing demeanor she shows during society meetings.
1042.weapon_desc: Twin puppets forged by Hades using an extremely rare Divine Grace fragment, the pride and joy of Hades the artist. As the duo are driven by Divine Power, they have a certain level of sentience and can thus operate even when Hades is not with them. They typically serve as maids at the Society of Muses where they take care of the members' day-to-day needs, though in combat they turn into fearsome weapons in the hands of Hades.

1119.name: Flowfly Mist
1119.hero_desc: From a practical point of view, Shu is really the one who handles Aether Gazer's administrative duties. She is not only the one responsible for training the future Administrator, she's also admired by her younger comrades and trusted by her seniors to help out with all sorts of tasks.
1119.impression: Quietly and quite out of the blue, the Administrator has become a key pillar of Division Nine. I've expected great things from you, Admin, ever since I became your mentor. But I didn't expect such tremendous progress from you, and frankly, there's nothing more gratifying for a teacher to see. No matter how strong you are, there are times you will get tired. Furthermore, an Administrator of Division Nine carries great responsibilities on their shoulders. You can always come to me if you need someone to lean on, Admin. You're my student, as well as someone who's personally important to me.
1119.weapon_desc: A pair of lances that came from a pendant gifted to Shu from a longtime friend, Tefnut. "Flowfly" is a shorter lance that can paralyze and incapacitate targets using the power of electricity, and "Mist" is a longer one with its blade permanently shrouded in thick fog.

1033.name: Enlightening
1033.hero_desc: One of the main people in charge of the Cryptics, she developed most of Aether Gazer's AI systems, including the Mimir system. For the sake of completely annihilating the Visbanes, she strives for precision and efficiency in everything she does.
1033.weapon_desc: An Access Key designed and developed by Heimdall herself, it's a masterpiece of photoelectric technology that allows her to control light. In addition to firing high-energy light beams, it can also use light diffusion to create zones on the battlefield that provide benefits to teammates.

1068.name: Cleansing Wind
1068.hero_desc: Oceanus' adopted son as well as student, he's currently studying sculpting at Stellaris Academy. He may look young, but he's quite reliable. Because Oceanus isn't able to care of himself very well, Enlil usually oversees his daily needs.
1068.weapon_desc: An Access Key containing the Divine Power of wind, it's usually sealed in a tome. When released, it allows the user to freely manipulate various forms of wind in combat.

1067.name: Backflowing
1067.hero_desc: A member of the Astral Council and the third judge, he has a supreme say in various Omorfies organizations and events. Usually unsmiling, he exudes an oppressive aura of indifference and is a harsh art critic.
1067.weapon_desc: The flowing breath of the sea entwines the body of the sword, which brims with the Divine Power of water. The user can extend it at will, wielding it like an all-reaching current.

1024.name: Jackal
1024.hero_desc: A CORG Egregious Crimes Department operative boasting an unprecedented 100% clearance rate. When it comes to missions, he tends to work solo and swiftly.
1024.weapon_desc: A mask that can be placed upon the deceased to copy its soul data, Anubis once used it to save the soul of the stray dog Upu. However, a soul's backup is not the same as the original—Anubis knows this very well, and for this reason he has never used this power on any other lives.

1028.name: Roaring Thunder
1028.hero_desc: Captain of Aether Gazer's Thunder Squad, and the fiercest fighter in the organization. Regardless of the problems that always arise on operations, they can always rely on Thor's rare power to complete the mission. With a strong sense of justice, but just like Thor's fierce combat style, she can often be too impulsive when handling matters.
1028.impression: If there's anything I have to say... it's that Admin works too hard. I mean, there's no reason for Admin to take charge of battle command and go to the frontlines with us, not when they have so much bothersome work to take care of! They even have to deal with that stupid cat Mimir... I'm already tired just thinking about all that. From now on, I will protect and watch over Admin! Although... while I may not be able to help Admin with their work, I sure can take care of everything on the battlefield. Just watch me as I send those Visbanes flying, one by one! None of them are getting anywhere near our Admin!
1028.weapon_desc: A colossal hammer that looks completely out of place next to Thor's unassuming frame was modified by the Cryptics. When used, it generates a storm force field that attacks the enemy with thunderbolts. It is equipped with the same high-performance electromagnetic module as the one in Thor's combat suit, which enables her to launch the giant hammer at high speed when inside the force field.

1052.name: Rage Serpent
1052.hero_desc: The head of the Akkadian Guild, he's worshipped by almost every bounty hunter in Rostach, though he seems to have some secret, inextricable link with CORG. He's usually looking after the residents of Rostach and loves adrenaline-pumping activities like arm wrestling. However, under that gregarious and friendly exterior seems to be some sort of hidden anxiety.
1052.weapon_desc: Marduk's trusty machine gun for many years. Rather than growing outdated with each tune-up, it actually gets even easier to use. The Rage Serpent was assigned to Marduk by the Gaea system at the time of his awakening. It can transform into a long-barreled EM gun, which Marduk calls the "Raging Dragon."

1017.name: Ailuros
1017.hero_desc: A CORG Egregious Crimes Department operative codenamed "Cat," though she's still an intern. Her colleagues affectionately call her "Kitty." She currently carries out a variety of missions with Anubis, who she calls her senior.
1017.weapon_desc: A six-piece blade set assigned to Bastet by the Gaea system at the time of her awakening. Its fierce-yet-stealthy attack mode has allowed Bastet to creep up on an opponent and swiftly end any encounter. It earned its name for its resemblance to a beast's claws glinting in the night.

1127.name: Countertide
1127.hero_desc:
Leviathan is always full of energy, and a real ditzy cutie pie.
She is naive and lively, but is unexpectedly the jealous sort. Do not act like you are close with Vidar in front of her.
1127.impression: Admin is really smart! Without Admin, I'd have failed Labbi's test and never activated my Access Key. And Admin's really capable too: it was Admin's tutoring that helped me pass my tests and get into the survey team. And oh, oh, Admin has helped walk Fenrir, bought me ice cream, and even told Zenkibo to go easy on me with her pranks... Admin has always taken such good care of me, and I want to always be with Admin, too. When I have Admin with me, it feels like I can do anything!
1127.weapon_desc: An umbrella-shaped Access Key Leviathan found on an island. It appears it had been there for quite some time, as it was found covered in dust. Activated once again with the awakening of Leviathan, it has the power of water and healing as well as the ability to control Labbi the AI.

1132.name: Firebrand
1132.hero_desc: Heir to the Valleyrand Family. After undertaking a joint venture with Aether Gazer, Tyr joined their Board of Directors and became the supervisor for Division Three. He rules with an iron fist, and treats business like war, striking fiercely and without remorse.
1132.weapon_desc: The young Tyr had his arm burned by the Visbane Garmr and became corrupted by Bane Energy. To protect him, his butler Hoenir gave Tyr his Access Key, named Firebrand, to suppress the Bane Energy. As the Valleyrand Family was then under threat, and Tyr's closest and dearest were in danger, he needed all the power he could get and so accepted the Access Key, no matter the cost. Thanks to this Access Key and the suppressed Bane Energy he somehow managed to harness, Tyr was able to protect his family and restore its glory.

1071.name: Azure Lord
1071.hero_desc:
Mengzhang, Deputy of Yuyi Isle, was the last of the deputies to join the Quad. He is also the most laid-back and free of the four.
He is rarely at his desk. In fact, it would be a major surprise to see him there. To find Mengzhang, one's best bet is to search the antique market.
1071.weapon_desc: A sword that has its origins in a jade "Gui" tablet owned by Mengzhang. The green jade is covered in an intricate scale pattern. When necessary, this Access Key can split into two, turning it into a weapon with dual characteristics: one left and one right, yin and yang.

1072.name: Omnisight
1072.hero_desc: Although it's hard for outsiders to believe, Luliang truly is the current president of Tian Lu Traders, and it's her business experience that has gotten the company to where it is today. She's also one of the people in charge of the Xu Heng District Modifiers.
1072.weapon_desc: Luliang is fiercely proud of the design of her retractable abacus and weapon. Fully extended, it serves as both a functional abacus and a convenient method of transportation.

1070.name: Tenblaze
1070.hero_desc:
Jinwu, born in Xu Heng, has studied the Astral Arcanum with her master Xihe in the mountains of Nanjiao Isle since she was a child. While she strives to uphold justice and righteousness, she can harbor rather grandiose ideas about herself sometimes.
On her master's instructions, she is currently traveling the world to expand her knowledge and hone her skills.
1070.weapon_desc: An exquisite and massive sword that can split into ten floating blades. According to Jinwu, such a complex and wonderful creation can only be controlled by a "Chosen One" like her.

1081.name: Waverender
1081.hero_desc: Skadi, who specializes in investigating signs of Visbane activity in the far-off oceans, is one of the very few Division Nine field Modifiers directly under Shu's command. While she appears a bit careless at first glance, when push comes to shove, she always shows the kind of drive a ship captain is expected to have.
1081.impression: What's Admin like? Hmm, how do I put it... I guess I'd say they're the type of person you'd follow into battle. When I'm with Admin, they always know what I'm thinking, even if I don't say a word, and they always take everyone's feelings into account. I always feel safe when Admin's around, and they've helped me achieve a lot of my dreams. In fact, my only dream at the moment is to go on adventures with Admin!
1081.weapon_desc: An Access Key that can transform into a small motorboat. Typically, it is carried on the user's back as equipment, providing firepower and maneuverability. It can also release low-temperature gas to create a layer of ice, allowing the motorboat to move freely regardless of the terrain.

1016.name: Wasteland Fiend
1016.hero_desc: Marduk's adopted son and the de facto second in command of the Akkadian Guild. Though arrogant and stonefaced, he is highly efficient and thorough when it comes to handling missions. A flexible thinker, wise commanders like him are a rare find for the Akkadian Guild.
1016.weapon_desc: The only "possession" the young Kingu brought with him out of the ruins. In principle, it works similarly to a chainsaw by dealing damage to enemy flesh and armor with its rapidly rotating saw teeth. In a fight, the user can hit a switch located at the hilt to activate the fuel motor to make the saw teeth rotate at high speed.

1074.name: Winged Gardener
1074.hero_desc:
HR Director at Tian Lu Traders. She may look indifferent but her mind is sharp, and constantly focused on improving efficiency.
Before the Awakening, she and her younger sister Linyu were dependent on each other to survive, and went through many hardships. She now enjoys traveling alone, and has accumulated all kinds of odd knowledge.
1074.weapon_desc: A pair of sturdy, well-made crutches able to store and release energy. It is said that Luliang spent a vast sum of money to have them custom made.

1075.name: Untainted Heart
1075.hero_desc:
Deputy of Nanjiao Isle at the Quad. A trained physician, she is keenly aware of the suffering that goes on in the world, and has established Vermilion Wellness along with several other medical halls on Nanjiao Isle to promote good health among the populace.
Lingguang is often seen in one of these halls treating the patients who come seeking help, and listens to them talk about their lives.
1075.weapon_desc: A pair of fans which light up with flame. The pieces that make up the frame of the fans can be launched at the enemy in the style of throwing knives. Where yin and yang intersect, the body is surrounded by fire.

1076.name: TaiYi
1076.hero_desc: Founder of the Quad and long-time protector of Xu Heng, Gengchen gets involved in all day-to-day affairs, no matter how big or small. She strives to maintain stability in Xu Heng in her own way. Everyone loves her and pays great respect to her, from the deputies to the common folk.
1076.weapon_desc: An artifact for channeling magic that's shaped like a jade pendant. Filled with thick ink, it looks like the whole universe flows within it.

1158.name: Madoibi Scorched
1158.hero_desc:
A potential candidate for Ryugiri, Kagutsuchi was chosen by the Karasugo family from among orphans and household servants all over the region.
Ranked nineteenth among the Mihakashisyuu officers, he faces elimination as a "useless person."
1158.weapon_desc: Ryugiri's form after no longer suppressing the Madoibi fire within it. The Crow God developed this weapon to use against its enemies, but it ultimately delivered the cut that beheaded the Crow God. Transformed by the hatred inside of it into a blade of corrupted fire, it's doubtful it will find peace until its enemies and master alike are reduced to ashes.

1049.name: Flower of Yomi
1049.hero_desc:
Izanami, originally named Karasugo Senba, was taken in by the Karasugo family 12 years ago. She came to be called a witch after being falsely accused of a crime. After devising a plan to kill the Crow God, she became the head of the Karasugo family behind the scenes.
She always seems rational and aloof in this role, even unapproachable, but she lets those close to her see her girlish side.
1049.weapon_desc: This crystal-clear blade can link Izanami's Divine Grace to the alter-dimension. Each swing generates a gust of air so cold, it's as if it came from the depths of the netherworld itself. Izanami relies on this to control the data of wandering spirits—Hisame, however, fights for herself.

1055.name: So-ei
1055.hero_desc:
A rogue vigilante of great renown from Sasanami's Shimogyou District, capable of wielding powerful ice Divine Power despite hating the cold.
Became aware of the nature of the world at a very young age, but lacking in a natural sense of purpose and refusing to believe that her identity as a Modifier means she necessarily has to fight the Visbanes led her to cultivate an interest in human society instead. Has always lived life by her own rules and desires.
1055.weapon_desc: Kuramitsuha's favorite naginata. Its blade is made entirely of ice that hardly ever breaks—and if it does, it's simply a matter of creating more ice to repair it.

1060.name: Nine-Tailed Guardian
1060.hero_desc: A member of the Tian Lu Traders security team who is often away on missions in Sephirah Zones outside of Xu Heng. Honest and straightforward, and well-liked by her teammates. Outspoken and brooks zero injustice around her.
1060.weapon_desc: A spear that's strong enough to crack open rocks and pierce through the darkness. Flames erupt from both ends during battle, and flutter in the air like burning tassels. Darkpiercer is the Access Key Luwu acquired when she awakened, and is her most trusted assistant.

1061.name: Ethereal Enigma
1061.hero_desc: The Quad representative for Shuofang Isle, and Xu Heng's foremost scholar and researcher. She's also one of the creators of the Astral Engine, and is responsible for all of its maintenance and upkeep.
1061.weapon_desc: This was once nothing but a broken shield, until Zhiming fit it with levitation technology and repurposed it as a portable vehicle and multi-functional test bed. The Access Key is actually made up of four floating shield fragments, which Zhiming can reconfigure at will using her Divine Power.

1150.name: Somezakura
1150.hero_desc: Buzenbo has trained in traditional kendo ever since she was little. Besides learning how to conquer her enemies with her blade, she's also absorbed the kendo spirit of protecting the weak, observing manners and restraint, and respecting her master.
1150.weapon_desc:
A long, cherry-red sword that Buzenbo used to carry with her everywhere before she was adopted. Its bright coloring is due to the incredible amount of Divine Power leaking out of it, making it perceptible even to humans.
This led Buzenbo's adoptive father to believe it was a cursed blade, so he sealed it away for many years before secretly giving it to Tsukuyomi when Buzenbo was old enough to leave home. Tsukuyomi can feel the blade's power but also its malice, meaning it should only be wielded by someone with the soul of a warrior.

1015.name: The Lioness
1015.hero_desc:
An operative holding a key position in the Quake Damage Control Department, Sekhmet is CORG's famed "lead problem solver."
Though a stunning, placid beauty in appearance, in practice, she's a reckless maniac. She's also a keen profiler that can bore into a person's innermost thoughts in a single casual conversation—naturally, dishonest or indolent colleagues and scheming crooks give her a wide berth. She can easily solve any tricky case she's tasked with.
1015.weapon_desc: A heavy weapon equipped with a crossbow that makes a terrifying screech when used. Originally designed for stealthy operation, Sekhmet intentionally damaged the Access Key's silencer module because she believes the loud mechanical roar it creates can trigger a kind of instinctive fear in her enemies, thus weakening their psychological defenses. When she first unveiled it, however, the people it seemed to affect the most were the allies standing too close to her.

1095.name: Gray Ibis
1095.hero_desc:
Captain of the CORG Egregious Crimes Department's special ops team, no one can gather intelligence better than she can. Uses information warfare to avoid direct confrontation with criminals and thus minimize the harm done to civilians.
With her top-level security clearance in CORG's Intel Department, it sometimes feels like she knows everybody's secrets. And she's not afraid to use them if someone is threatening to impede the progress of a mission. In fact, there's little she won't stoop to if it means getting the mission done.
1095.weapon_desc: A throwing knife disguised as an ornament. Throw it directly at the enemy to attack, or control it with a special silk thread. It is worth noting that this special silk thread seems to be made with the same silk thread used to hold together Thoth's clothing...

1284.name: Dimglare
1284.hero_desc: Verthandi learned the truth about herself and her past during the Hyperspace experiments, further cementing her desire to protect others. Now able to wield both Divine Grace and Bane Energy at the same time, she has a whole new attitude.
1284.weapon_desc: The long sword appeared in response to the girl's will. The great flash that appears along its length is one that spans the past and the future. Verthandi is able to drive the Access Key with her will alone and summon a giant sword-wielding arm made of Divine Grace. However, Verthandi has yet to fully master the power of this Access Key, and many unknowns remain.

1197.name: Dreamshade
1197.hero_desc: A Modifier with the ability to enter and invite others to enter dreams. Unable to fully control this ability, however, Hades has taken her into the Society of Muses, where Hades' two puppet maids look after her.
1197.weapon_desc:
An Access Key that helps Oneiroi to manage her dreams. Since she is unable to fully control her dreams at the moment, Phobetor and Hades have agreed to look after Oneiroi in her dreams as her "supervisors".
Helps Oneiroi expand her giant dreamscapes that pulls others into them. It is said that if Oneiroi unleashes her dreamscapes at full power while in this state, she can even affect the fabric of reality.

1022.name: Serene Moon
1022.hero_desc: Holder of the fifth seat of the Astral Council of Omorfies and President of the Choir Association, she is permanently stationed on the Omorfies island of Krete. Her cold and aloof personality often makes her difficult to approach.
1022.weapon_desc: Made up of a gun and a staff, this Access Key is embedded with a core unit that controls the vibrations of sound waves. This then affects objects or creatures within range, almost as if the sound takes them over.

1021.name: Dawnray
1021.hero_desc: Former Deputy Commander of the Knights of Convallaria, she now serves as Commander of the Knights of the Lighthouse. Descended from an aristocratic family of Omorfies and a pupil of Selene, holder of the fifth seat of the Astral Council. Upright and disciplined, she was even senior to Athena in the Knights of Convallaria.
1021.weapon_desc:
This sword has been with Artemis since her childhood. It is a symbol of her chivalry and a manifestation of the young girl's will.
When the body of the sword becomes infused with Divine Power, its musical notes become solid, playing a beautiful melody as she swings the sword.

1020.name: Trimūrti
1020.hero_desc:
The founder of Meruism who has delegated the gang's affairs to others for years while she shut herself away to study the Book of All Past.
With a dynamic personality, she always jumps at the chance to take advantage of others, and when it comes to business, she's confident and decisive, always following through on what she's set her mind on.
1020.weapon_desc: The golden orb that floats beside Brahmā is also a symbol of Brahmā's powers of creation and destruction. When Brahmā decides to exert her destructive power, Bionica will show its true form and summon a trident with the power of annihilation. Don't get too close when this happens—there's a risk you'll be vaporized.

1156.name: Annihilator
1156.hero_desc:
The "big sister" of Meruism. While she's not actually much older and she's rather blunt and straightforward, Kali does think of herself as an older sister.
She takes it upon herself to care for the orphaned and displaced children her organization takes in, and feels disgusted at the sight of the devastation caused by the Visbanes.
Kali has accrued lots of life experience and survival skills in Shashvat, namely haggling and cooking...
1156.weapon_desc: A bracelet which contains the raging power of lightning. Just putting it on makes it difficult to control the electricity pouring out of it. Even Kali finds it hard to control this powerful force completely, so she only uses this Access Key as a last resort.

1089.name: Tempest
1089.hero_desc:
The second-in-command of Meruism, she usually looks exhausted. She's always procrastinating, skipping out on work, or formulating a plan on how to skip work the next time.
The only time she gets serious is when there's a problem that nobody else can handle. At those times, it becomes evident that she possesses extraordinary analytical and problem-solving abilities, putting her intelligence to use to solve just about any problem that's put in front of her.
1089.weapon_desc: Twin guns that harness energy, channel it, and convert it into powerful shock waves. The impact effect varies according to the type of energy bullet loaded. Parvati is pleased with the fact that the tanks are disposable and replaceable, eliminating the need for tedious recharging.

6073.name: Darkstar - Hel event
6073.weapon_desc: An AI known internally as Ganglati. This rather plain-looking coffin transforms into a powerful arsenal. While full of gripes and vicious of tongue, it becomes as quiet as a church mouse once it is put on the receiving end of a scolding.

6103.name: Shinku
6103.weapon_desc: The blade is said to have been brought by Yatagarasu and once served as an important treasure for Sasanami to guard its national fortunes, but was later lost in a civil war. It is known to the world as the ancestor of katanas.

6104.name: Somezakura
6104.weapon_desc:
A long, cherry-red sword that Buzenbo used to carry with her everywhere before she was adopted. Its bright coloring is due to the incredible amount of Divine Power leaking out of it, making it perceptible even to humans.
This led Buzenbo's adoptive father to believe it was a cursed blade, so he sealed it away for many years before secretly giving it to Tsukuyomi when Buzenbo was old enough to leave home. Tsukuyomi can feel the blade's power but also its malice, meaning it should only be wielded by someone with the soul of a warrior.

6105.name: New Pact
6105.weapon_desc: This longsword, which symbolizes destiny and fate, was previously a holy sword known throughout the world. Its wielders were all heroes who achieved glorious feats, or the ones chosen by this sword were fated to become heroes from the very beginning. The ridge of the sword is engraved with a line of unreadable ancient Runic text. It seems to be an ancient poetic ballad from an icy region.

10097.name: Dreamshade
10097.hero_desc: A Modifier with the ability to enter and invite others to enter dreams. Unable to fully control this ability, however, Hades has taken her into the Society of Muses, where Hades' two puppet maids look after her.
10097.weapon_desc: A servant who manages Oneiroi's dreams on her behalf, he has his own independent consciousness and calls himself Phobetor the butler. Helps Oneiroi expand her giant dreamscapes that pulls others into them. It is said that unleashing her dreamscapes at full power can even affect the fabric of reality.
